PROCEDURE:-  
1. Open Visual Studio by clicking StartðŸ¡ªAll ProgramsðŸ¡ªMicrosoft Visual Studio.  
2. To create a Console application Select ProjectsðŸ¡ªNew project and click on Console application icon.  
3. In the name text box type the name of the Console application and click OK. 
4. The screen changes to coding window. 
5. Type the code inside Static void Main(string[] args)  
6. Press F5 to execute the application. 


CODING:-  
static void Main(string[] args)  
{ 
Console.WriteLine("Enter a Alphabet");  
char ch = Convert.ToChar(Console.ReadLine()); if(char.IsUpper(ch)) { Console.WriteLine("Upper case");  
}  
else if(char.IsLower(ch)) { Console.WriteLine("Lower case");  
} else { Console.WriteLine("Other character");  
} Console.ReadLine(); 
} 
